basics.summary: i a software developer from, victoria. i started study at swinburne university in 2009 and received my bachelor with honours in 2013. during my time at swinburne i was involved in a number of scholarship programs, received a number of achievement awards, and began tutoring for the university s introduction to programming unit during my third year. nearing the completion of my bachelor degree, i decided to engage in the university s honours program and undertook a year of research in automating the development of mobile applications, in which i received some success with my work being showcased at the ddd conference in 2013. since the completion of my degree i have been working with the / swinburne software innovation lab in a variety of projects utilising cutting edge technologies and leveraging the resources available at the university in the pursuit of solving problems faced by australian industry.
